Discharge Grade: B Discharge Remarks: Overall Q uncertainty = 3.0% (ISO). Good measurement overall considering the conditions. Control Condition Remarks: Large ice formation in middle of control riffle causing flow to separate around it. Most flow going to right side of ice dam. Significant slush flowing in channel (1 - 5m dia, 0.1 - 0.2m depth). Slush covers 90% of water surface at gauge where flow constricted and 40-50% downstream 50m of gauge where channel widens.  Ice formed on both sides of channel, particularly on left side at riffle.  Major ice pans flowing during measurement (50% of water surface covered in slush pans that were 1-5m dia and 0.1-0.2m depth). Dueto ice pans did not use 0.2/0.8 method for panels greater than 0.75m depth as the 0.2 depth shot was significantly affected by ice pansdistrubing velocity and hitting probe. Used 0.6 method for entire measurement. Ice pans were hitting rod during measurement causing jerks in rod and sudden tilts in rod angle, expect warnings. Best location available.
